03:13.784 --> 03:16.396
♪ Doesn't he notice? ♪

03:16.420 --> 03:18.431
♪ Can he read your lips? ♪

03:18.455 --> 03:20.200
♪ If I were with you still ♪

03:20.224 --> 03:22.435
♪ I would know how to back down ♪

03:22.459 --> 03:24.103
♪ No ♪

03:24.127 --> 03:28.741
♪ And your fragile heart
I'd handle with care ♪

03:28.765 --> 03:33.413
♪ Maintain it on display
up on a shelf ♪

03:33.437 --> 03:38.284
♪ No, he doesn't know
how to keep you near ♪

03:38.308 --> 03:43.289
♪ It ain't no roses,
no, you can't buy love ♪

03:43.313 --> 03:45.925
♪ You, ooh, ooh ♪

03:45.949 --> 03:47.527
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

03:47.551 --> 03:49.963
♪ I'm saying I'm better for you ♪

03:49.987 --> 03:51.965
♪ Baby, I'm better for you ♪

03:51.989 --> 03:53.132
♪ I don't know what to call it ♪

03:53.156 --> 03:55.602
♪ You, ooh, ooh ♪

03:55.626 --> 03:57.303
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

03:57.327 --> 03:59.339
♪ I'm saying I'm better for you ♪

03:59.363 --> 04:02.242
♪ Baby, I'm better for you ♪

04:02.266 --> 04:04.310
Look, I know we all holding
drinks in our hands,

04:04.334 --> 04:05.612
but he is thirsty as hell.

04:05.636 --> 04:06.913
Quiet, Porsha!

04:06.937 --> 04:08.915
He's also fine.

04:08.939 --> 04:10.717
Speaking of, where's Andre?

04:10.741 --> 04:12.385
Ain't he hosting
this little after-party?

04:12.409 --> 04:13.720
Uh, I'm sure he's at home

04:13.744 --> 04:15.755
with his very pregnant,
very beautiful wife.

04:15.779 --> 04:17.757
Also, I'm not my boss's keeper.

04:17.781 --> 04:19.392
Uh, when I was Cookie's assistant,

04:19.416 --> 04:20.593
if I didn't have eyes on her,

04:20.617 --> 04:22.328
you bet damn well sure
somebody else did.

04:22.352 --> 04:24.597
Well, then I guess it's great
that Cookie is not CEO.

04:24.621 --> 04:26.332
And neither is Lucious,
for that matter.

04:26.356 --> 04:30.303
♪ Maintain it on display
up on a shelf ♪

04:30.327 --> 04:31.871
Mm-hmm, I say "amen" to that.

04:31.895 --> 04:34.173
Uh, you need to be saying
"amen" to that.

04:34.197 --> 04:35.608
♪ To keep you near ♪

04:35.632 --> 04:37.443
♪ It ain't no roses ♪

04:37.467 --> 04:41.281
♪ No, you can't buy love ♪

04:43.707 --> 04:46.152
That kombucha went right through me.

04:46.176 --> 04:48.193
I'll be quick.

04:50.614 --> 04:53.159
Listen...

04:53.183 --> 04:55.228
we get this money from Uncle Ray,

04:55.252 --> 04:56.563
and by this time tomorrow,

04:56.587 --> 05:00.138
we are drinking from coconuts, okay?

05:24.848 --> 05:26.359
- Hello?
- Hey.

05:26.383 --> 05:27.694
How'd the launch go?

05:27.718 --> 05:29.529
Oh, strong, Pop.

05:29.553 --> 05:31.064
Real strong.

05:31.088 --> 05:33.733
- How's it going on your end?
- I don't know.

05:33.757 --> 05:35.001
We're at a gas station,

05:35.025 --> 05:37.070
like, 30 miles
outside of Saratoga Springs.

05:38.228 --> 05:41.007
You sound winded, man. You all right?

05:41.031 --> 05:42.675
I'm just taking out the trash, Pop.

05:43.700 --> 05:44.744
Don't worry. I'm good.

05:44.768 --> 05:46.346
Were you able to confirm

05:46.370 --> 05:49.182
that this Uncle Ray
is Damon's money man

05:49.206 --> 05:50.850
that the guy Yana's been talking to?

05:52.209 --> 05:54.754
I couldn't get his last name,
but I think so.

05:54.778 --> 05:57.724
Word is this Ray is extra cautious.

05:57.748 --> 06:00.526
Runs Damon's entire operation
on an air-gapped laptop.

06:00.550 --> 06:02.695
Every client, account, and amount.

06:02.719 --> 06:04.464
That laptop is what you need
to clear your name.

06:04.488 --> 06:05.465
Great.

06:05.489 --> 06:06.866
You talk to your mama?

06:06.890 --> 06:08.401
I mean, anything from her?

06:09.459 --> 06:10.903
No, nothing yet.

06:24.775 --> 06:27.420
That was so much better, Lala!
That was really great!

06:27.444 --> 06:29.455
Yeah, I could almost hear you at...

06:29.479 --> 06:32.664
- Don't... don't look at her.
- That time.

06:33.817 --> 06:36.229
Can I talk to you for a minute
outside, please?

06:36.253 --> 06:38.403
- Uh, to me?
- Yeah.

06:40.190 --> 06:41.167
Come on, you're gonna scare her!

06:41.191 --> 06:42.168
Girl, you know what?

06:42.192 --> 06:43.569
Yo, you trying to scare her?

06:43.593 --> 06:45.371
We have been trying to get
Lala to sing all day

06:45.395 --> 06:46.873
and all night, for that matter.

06:46.897 --> 06:48.307
You need to just face it,

06:48.331 --> 06:51.544
your Internet phenom
is just not phenomenal.

06:51.568 --> 06:54.714
Okay. Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis
probably felt the same way

06:54.738 --> 06:56.315
the first night
they worked with Janet.

06:56.339 --> 06:58.618
She don't do nothing
but whisper on all them songs

06:58.642 --> 07:00.586
but they be hits, right?

07:00.610 --> 07:01.921
You just got to give her time!

07:01.945 --> 07:03.856
Time is something we do not have.

07:03.880 --> 07:08.261
After all that money we spent
signing Ms. Lalaland,

07:08.285 --> 07:11.497
we don't have any more money
to sign anybody else.

07:11.521 --> 07:12.865
We might as well just cut our losses.

07:12.889 --> 07:14.167
No, no, no, no, no.
Look, look, look, look...

07:14.191 --> 07:16.469
- Let's just...
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

07:16.493 --> 07:19.338
We are not cutting our losses
right now, okay?

07:19.362 --> 07:20.573
Okay, but I'm shaking.

07:20.597 --> 07:22.675
I finally sat you down
and made you listen to her.

07:22.699 --> 07:24.410
I know you heard what I heard.

07:24.434 --> 07:26.446
She is special, okay?

07:26.470 --> 07:28.014
She's gonna be a major
hit-maker for us.

07:28.038 --> 07:29.115
You can see that.

07:29.139 --> 07:30.183
I know, but what we need right now

07:30.207 --> 07:32.785
is a home run to stay afloat,

07:32.809 --> 07:35.855
and she's not even getting us
over the ten-yard line.

07:35.879 --> 07:37.490
You're mixing your metaphors!

07:37.514 --> 07:39.659
Okay, you're sleepy.

07:39.683 --> 07:40.793
Yes!

07:40.817 --> 07:42.528
♪ It's all in me ♪

07:42.552 --> 07:43.996
I know you're tired.

07:44.020 --> 07:46.265
Look, I am so tired.

07:46.289 --> 07:48.434
I cannot listen to her anymore.

07:48.458 --> 07:50.803
Can we just fix her tomorrow, please?

07:50.827 --> 07:53.639
♪ I'm every woman ♪

07:53.663 --> 07:55.141
♪ It's all in me ♪

07:55.165 --> 07:58.010
I think I know how
to fix her before breakfast.

07:58.034 --> 08:00.446
And also, I need to get a drink
in you because I...

08:00.470 --> 08:02.682
Ugh!

08:11.448 --> 08:13.693
Oh, God, no.

08:13.717 --> 08:16.996
Oh, no, no, no, no.
Come on, baby, wake up.

08:19.156 --> 08:21.300
911 operator, what's your emergency?

08:21.324 --> 08:23.536
My wife, she's... she's bleeding.

08:23.560 --> 08:25.171
She's unresponsive.

08:25.195 --> 08:27.173
She's eight months pregnant.
I need help now, please.

08:28.498 --> 08:29.842
She's not breathing.

08:29.866 --> 08:31.744
All right. Come on, baby.

08:31.768 --> 08:33.212
Come on, baby.

08:33.236 --> 08:34.547
Come on.

08:34.571 --> 08:39.018
Come on!

08:39.042 --> 08:40.620
Don't you die on me, come on!

08:40.644 --> 08:42.288
Come on, baby!

08:44.147 --> 08:46.264
Come on, baby!

08:52.844 --> 08:55.322
Andre!

08:55.346 --> 08:56.623
Andre. Where's my mom?

08:56.647 --> 08:58.225
Is she okay?

08:58.249 --> 09:00.127
She stopped breathing.

09:00.151 --> 09:02.696
They were able to get her heart
going again in the ambulance.

09:02.720 --> 09:04.798
- What, she died?
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

09:04.822 --> 09:07.301
Quincy, your mother's strong,
brother, she's strong.

09:07.325 --> 09:08.635
What's going on? Is she okay?

09:08.659 --> 09:10.103
She's still unconscious.

09:10.127 --> 09:12.072
She may have hit her head
when she fell.

09:12.096 --> 09:13.073
What about the baby?

09:13.097 --> 09:14.274
Teri's lost a lot of blood,

09:14.298 --> 09:15.943
and the baby's heart rate is abnormal,

09:15.967 --> 09:17.244
a sign of fetal distress.

09:17.268 --> 09:18.645
We think it's best to move forward

09:18.669 --> 09:20.147
with an emergency C-section.

09:20.171 --> 09:21.915
Anything you have to do to
save them, Doctor, you do it.

09:21.939 --> 09:23.150
Well, that's the thing, Mr. Lyon.

09:23.174 --> 09:25.252
Teri has developed
late-term preeclampsia,

09:25.276 --> 09:27.287
and her blood pressure
is still spiking.

09:27.311 --> 09:28.989
If we do the C-section right away,

09:29.013 --> 09:31.291
there's a good chance
we can save the baby...

09:31.315 --> 09:33.160
but Teri is at risk
of further hemorrhaging.

09:33.184 --> 09:34.428
No, you can't let my mother die!

09:34.452 --> 09:36.363
We do the most good where we can

09:36.387 --> 09:38.131
and what we know right now
is we can save the baby,

09:38.155 --> 09:41.301
but if we wait,
they both remain at risk...

09:41.325 --> 09:43.604
possibly grave risk.

09:43.628 --> 09:46.373
You're gonna have to make a choice...

09:46.397 --> 09:48.175
and make it soon.

09:48.199 --> 09:50.115
Thank you, Doctor.

09:58.142 --> 09:59.319
Quincy.

09:59.343 --> 10:01.154
No, you can't let them
kill my mother, man!

10:01.178 --> 10:02.656
I'm Teri's husband, okay?

10:02.680 --> 10:04.858
I have final say on decisions
about her and the baby.

10:04.882 --> 10:07.461
- I got this, brother...
- For six months!

10:07.485 --> 10:08.929
For six months,
you've been her husband.

10:08.953 --> 10:11.298
But you and I have known each
other a lot longer, haven't we?

10:11.322 --> 10:13.634
Look, you saved my life,
but this is different.

10:13.658 --> 10:15.936
Quincy...

10:15.960 --> 10:18.038
Brother, hear me.

10:18.062 --> 10:19.773
I love your mother just as much
as you do, brother.

10:19.797 --> 10:21.041
I love her.

10:21.065 --> 10:22.709
We're gonna save her, too.

10:22.733 --> 10:24.945
You got my word on that, man.

10:28.472 --> 10:31.318
We're gonna save her, too.

10:31.342 --> 10:33.387
You're stalling, Damon.

10:33.411 --> 10:35.589
So I'm watching this TV show you on,

10:35.613 --> 10:37.691
and, um...

10:37.715 --> 10:41.228
One queen can't class up
a barn full of heifers.

10:41.252 --> 10:42.529
But I get it.

10:42.553 --> 10:44.431
You had to do something
to forget about us.

10:45.456 --> 10:46.867
You think I want you?

10:46.891 --> 10:48.669
Are you out your rabid-ass mind?

10:48.693 --> 10:49.903
You here, ain't you?

10:49.927 --> 10:52.773
Okay, so I tip you off
about the damn Feds,

10:52.797 --> 10:54.875
and to save your own ass,

10:54.899 --> 10:58.011
you sic that thirsty bitch
Conway on Lucious instead.

10:58.035 --> 11:01.281
- It's called survival.
- No, that's called betrayal.

11:01.305 --> 11:03.450
So the man who opened his heart to me

11:03.474 --> 11:04.718
about his daughter's cancer,

11:04.742 --> 11:06.820
who held my hand
when Andre was touch and go,

11:06.844 --> 11:08.155
where did he go?

11:08.179 --> 11:09.656
Because we've been through a lot,

11:09.680 --> 11:13.026
and I'm trying to understand
why you would do me so dirty.

11:14.051 --> 11:15.329
Who dat?

11:15.353 --> 11:16.663
Lucious?

11:16.687 --> 11:19.399
Trying to tell you
how to play me, huh?

11:22.393 --> 11:24.905
That's exactly what that's about.

11:24.929 --> 11:29.081
I don't need instructions
from him or from you.

11:31.535 --> 11:33.947
You see, I'm a queen.

11:33.971 --> 11:36.717
And queens can never
be anybody's pawn.

11:38.442 --> 11:41.154
Now answer my damn question.

11:52.189 --> 11:53.500
You know what I was thinking?

11:53.524 --> 11:54.935
What?

11:54.959 --> 11:56.970
Eleuthera.

11:56.994 --> 11:58.305
Yeah.

11:58.329 --> 12:00.641
I always wanted to go there.

12:00.665 --> 12:01.908
I've never been,

12:01.932 --> 12:05.112
but I hear they have
100 little islands

12:05.136 --> 12:08.315
that are all filled with
white sand and clear water.

12:08.339 --> 12:11.885
Yeah, I could build a nice
house on the beach for us,

12:11.909 --> 12:16.723
dig a well, go fishing every day.

12:16.747 --> 12:20.794
And that makes you what,
CEO of the beach?

12:20.818 --> 12:24.798
Lucious, that's not freedom.
That is a responsibility.

12:24.822 --> 12:27.334
I want to protect you.

12:27.358 --> 12:29.336
I want to take care of you.

12:29.360 --> 12:31.338
- That's what I do.
- Mm-hmm.

12:31.362 --> 12:33.240
Let me be me, come on!

12:33.264 --> 12:36.109
That's how I built Empire, you know?

12:36.133 --> 12:40.213
You built Empire so that
you could take care of people?

12:40.237 --> 12:42.282
I mean, that had
something to do with it.

12:42.306 --> 12:44.851
Lucious, if you don't stop...

12:44.875 --> 12:47.788
You built Empire so that
you could be the king.

12:47.812 --> 12:50.190
♪ The wind, it cries... ♪

12:50.214 --> 12:52.626
Don't you get tired
of wearing that crown?

12:52.650 --> 12:54.361
I think you should just imagine

12:54.385 --> 12:57.064
how free you'd be
if you just took it off.

12:57.088 --> 12:58.398
It's easy to talk about freedom

12:58.422 --> 13:01.702
when you got a daddy
that's bankrolling you

13:01.726 --> 13:03.804
and keeping you afloat, you know?

13:03.828 --> 13:07.340
Lucious, you need to let it go.

13:07.364 --> 13:09.976
You got to let go
of all of that responsibility

13:10.000 --> 13:11.645
and all that obligation.

13:14.839 --> 13:18.652
I don't want our island
to be an Empire.

13:18.676 --> 13:21.154
Empires fall.

13:21.178 --> 13:22.956
I want it to be forever.

13:22.980 --> 13:25.559
♪ Downstream ♪

13:25.583 --> 13:28.829
♪ 'Cause the life they lived... ♪

13:28.853 --> 13:30.697
Well, we're here.

13:32.022 --> 13:36.570
♪ And the wind screams Mary ♪

13:41.932 --> 13:43.677
Andre.

13:43.701 --> 13:45.245
Pastor Brown.

13:45.269 --> 13:46.747
I came as soon as I heard.

13:46.771 --> 13:49.116
The doctors want to take
the baby as soon as possible.

13:49.140 --> 13:50.117
Now, Teri, she... she...

13:50.141 --> 13:52.219
I understand. I understand, brother.

13:52.243 --> 13:53.353
I-I don't... I don't know what to do.

13:53.377 --> 13:55.622
H-He's doing it again.

13:55.646 --> 13:57.424
Oh, He's just doing it again, man.

13:57.448 --> 13:59.259
Andre.

13:59.283 --> 14:02.429
Teri has shared with me
everything you've been through.

14:02.453 --> 14:03.630
God gets her through all of that.

14:03.654 --> 14:06.566
It never stops, this God!

14:06.590 --> 14:08.235
Oh, God, He...

14:08.259 --> 14:10.103
God is pushing me, man.

14:10.127 --> 14:11.371
Oh, He's pushing me.

14:11.395 --> 14:12.639
- He's not pushing you.
- He's pushing me.

14:12.663 --> 14:15.842
He's building.

14:15.866 --> 14:17.043
You know, you remind me of Abraham.

14:17.067 --> 14:18.044
Oh, Abraham.

14:18.068 --> 14:19.846
You've tried to be obedient,

14:19.870 --> 14:22.249
but God keeps challenging your faith.

14:22.273 --> 14:24.351
He has a higher calling
for you, Andre.

14:24.375 --> 14:26.586
All you have to do is let go
and let God...

14:26.610 --> 14:28.455
This is not about me, Pastor.
It's not about me.

14:28.479 --> 14:31.091
It's about Teri.
We keep this about Teri.

14:31.115 --> 14:32.864
Then let's pray for Teri.

14:41.058 --> 14:42.936
Heavenly Father,
we come to You praying

14:42.960 --> 14:44.960
that You pour Your anointed
grace over this family.

14:46.263 --> 14:48.108
Andre is a good man,

14:48.132 --> 14:49.476
a family man,

14:49.500 --> 14:53.747
a God-fearing man
deserving of God's grace.

14:53.771 --> 14:55.487
Help him tonight, dear Lord.

14:59.476 --> 15:01.154
What's the matter?

15:07.651 --> 15:10.297
God can't help me.

15:10.321 --> 15:12.833
- But you have to have faith.
- I do have faith.

15:14.792 --> 15:17.170
Faith that I love my wife.

15:17.194 --> 15:18.572
Faith that I love my child

15:18.596 --> 15:22.242
more than I can ever love
anything in this world...

15:22.266 --> 15:24.611
but I will not have faith

15:24.635 --> 15:27.848
in a God who would rather push me

15:27.872 --> 15:30.083
than protect my family.

15:30.107 --> 15:31.785
No.

15:34.812 --> 15:36.756
You can't control this, Andre.

15:36.780 --> 15:38.658
Thanks for coming out, Pastor.

15:38.682 --> 15:42.462
I appreciate it, I do.

15:42.486 --> 15:45.332
I'll make the decision myself, okay?

15:55.599 --> 15:57.244
Uncle Ray's isn't far.

15:57.268 --> 15:58.578
I'll be back soon.

15:58.602 --> 16:00.380
It's all right. I'll go with you.

16:00.404 --> 16:02.015
No one else can go to Uncle Ray's.

16:02.039 --> 16:03.750
I shouldn't have let you
come this far as it is.

16:03.774 --> 16:05.752
Look, I'll just sit
in the car and wait.

16:05.776 --> 16:07.687
I mean, it's dangerous
out here, you know?

16:07.711 --> 16:09.356
I am fine.

16:09.380 --> 16:11.224
I don't make a lot of promises
to my father,

16:11.248 --> 16:13.226
but this one I can't break.

16:13.250 --> 16:15.834
I'll be back.

16:30.267 --> 16:32.479
- Hey.
- Yeah?

16:32.503 --> 16:33.813
You know what?

16:33.837 --> 16:35.715
I forgot to tell you something.

16:35.739 --> 16:37.817
What?

16:37.841 --> 16:39.486
Thank you.

16:39.510 --> 16:40.820
Thank you for what?

16:40.844 --> 16:42.155
For everything.

16:42.179 --> 16:46.192
I mean, for your honesty,
for the money, and...

16:46.216 --> 16:48.395
giving me a new chance at life.

16:48.419 --> 16:51.298
- Mm.
- I'm ready.

16:55.893 --> 16:58.138
I love you, Lucious.

16:59.630 --> 17:03.310
Write a song for me while I'm gone.

17:36.734 --> 17:39.212
There's been no change in
Teri's condition or the baby's.

17:39.236 --> 17:40.647
We're still concerned about her
elevated blood...

17:40.671 --> 17:42.320
Did she wake up?

17:43.774 --> 17:45.123
No.

17:46.577 --> 17:48.793
I've made a decision.

17:50.347 --> 17:52.125
You're gonna save them both.

17:53.617 --> 17:55.528
I'm sorry, Mr. Lyon.
I can't guarantee that...

17:55.552 --> 17:57.163
Okay, I understand all that,

17:57.187 --> 17:59.032
but the fact still remains, okay?

17:59.056 --> 18:00.300
I don't care what you have to do.

18:00.324 --> 18:01.768
Get two sets of surgeons in there,

18:01.792 --> 18:02.969
one for the baby, one for my wife.

18:02.993 --> 18:04.137
I don't care
how many doctors it takes,

18:04.161 --> 18:05.538
and I don't care how much it costs.

18:05.562 --> 18:07.841
Mr. Lyon, it doesn't work like that.

18:07.865 --> 18:11.378
You are gonna save them both,
do you understand me?

18:19.162 --> 18:20.573
Look me in the eye.

18:20.597 --> 18:23.943
Tell me you didn't
tell the Feds about Lucious.

18:23.967 --> 18:25.378
I swear to you, Cookie,

18:25.402 --> 18:28.381
I ain't never snitched
a day in my life.

18:28.405 --> 18:29.854
Till now.

18:32.943 --> 18:35.885
Okay, when the Feds
came down on Lucious,

18:35.886 --> 18:36.996
it wasn't just him.

18:37.020 --> 18:38.698
They hit me and my sons hard.

18:38.722 --> 18:40.600
Like, why would you do that to me?

18:40.624 --> 18:42.302
I did it for you.

18:42.326 --> 18:44.938
I did it to make him
let go of you, Cookie.

18:46.463 --> 18:50.677
So you did that so that you
could free me from Lucious.

18:50.701 --> 18:52.045
- Yeah.
- What?

18:52.069 --> 18:53.713
You don't think you worth it?

18:53.737 --> 18:55.215
Damon...

18:55.239 --> 18:58.918
you did it because you thought
I'd come running to you.

18:58.942 --> 19:01.254
I did it to free you from the hold

19:01.278 --> 19:03.690
the man has had on you
your whole life.

19:03.714 --> 19:04.824
I'm talking about

19:04.848 --> 19:06.392
a hold he got on you from behind bars,

19:06.416 --> 19:08.661
from across boardrooms,

19:08.685 --> 19:12.432
from wherever he is hiding now.

19:12.456 --> 19:15.273
He does not deserve you.

19:16.727 --> 19:19.072
If that make me a snitch, so be it.

19:19.096 --> 19:20.907
I can live with it.

19:20.931 --> 19:23.910
You don't get to tell me
who I can and cannot love.

19:23.934 --> 19:26.813
So you need to stay in your damn lane.

19:26.837 --> 19:28.181
You know what?

19:28.205 --> 19:30.850
If the reason why you came
over here was to help him,

19:30.874 --> 19:32.819
that don't have to be
the reason why you stay.

19:34.745 --> 19:37.557
You a grown-ass woman, Cookie.

19:37.581 --> 19:40.994
You deserve some love
from a grown-ass man.

19:50.360 --> 19:52.171
♪ Can't we just talk? ♪

19:53.196 --> 19:54.440
♪ Can't we just talk? ♪

19:54.464 --> 19:55.875
Hey!

19:55.899 --> 19:58.745
The kickoff party was lit,
and so is this after-party!

19:58.769 --> 20:00.113
Hey!

20:00.137 --> 20:04.250
Is there any doubt that Empire
is not all the way back?

20:04.274 --> 20:08.254
♪ I've never felt like this before ♪

20:08.278 --> 20:10.990
Oh, my God.

20:11.014 --> 20:12.992
I hope everything's okay.

20:13.016 --> 20:14.761
Listen, I'm sending out
my love and my prayers

20:14.785 --> 20:15.995
to Teri and Andre.

20:16.019 --> 20:17.931
God's got you.

20:17.955 --> 20:19.966
To all my people watching this live,

20:19.990 --> 20:23.069
please put them and their baby
in your prayers,

20:23.093 --> 20:25.772
because all life is precious.

20:25.796 --> 20:27.640
All right, y'all, I'm out.

20:27.664 --> 20:30.243
Thank y'all for coming, man.
Appreciate it.

20:30.267 --> 20:31.644
You look nice.

20:31.668 --> 20:34.047
- Hey, stranger.
- What's up, T?

20:34.071 --> 20:35.782
Can we talk?

20:35.806 --> 20:37.216
You ever get that feeling like

20:37.240 --> 20:39.485
the music's just
not where you want it to be?

20:39.509 --> 20:40.820
All the time.

20:40.844 --> 20:44.624
I mean, I feel like it's
just a part of the process.

20:44.648 --> 20:46.893
But then I just got to
re-center myself,

20:46.917 --> 20:49.128
remember what I'm trying to say...

20:49.152 --> 20:50.897
and put in the work to change it.

20:50.921 --> 20:52.231
I just feel like
I should've said something

20:52.255 --> 20:54.267
when I had the chance to, you know?

20:54.291 --> 20:56.502
It's like every song
on my album... every song...

20:56.526 --> 20:57.937
sounds the same.

20:57.961 --> 21:01.674
Look, Lucious wanted me to be Rihanna.

21:01.698 --> 21:04.277
Eddie wanted me to be Beyoncé.

21:04.301 --> 21:08.681
But it... it took me a while to
realize that they got Tiana.

21:09.806 --> 21:12.518
And I'm everything, okay?

21:12.542 --> 21:14.020
You got to take charge,

21:14.044 --> 21:16.356
or you gonna be caught in
somebody else's game forever.

21:16.380 --> 21:18.825
So you want me to walk over
to Andre and be like,

21:18.849 --> 21:20.126
"Run it up, dog.

21:20.150 --> 21:21.661
I need all of my music back."

21:21.685 --> 21:24.998
I mean, it's your music.
It's your career.

21:25.022 --> 21:27.300
♪ Now I'm on the way ♪

21:27.324 --> 21:30.036
You don't know your own power.

21:35.198 --> 21:36.809
Hello?

21:36.833 --> 21:39.045
- You coming?
- Where we going?

21:39.069 --> 21:40.780
You said it all sounds the same,

21:40.804 --> 21:42.548
so let's go change it.

21:42.572 --> 21:46.552
Studio 3 is open,
and it's now or ever.

21:54.051 --> 21:55.328
Shots!

21:55.352 --> 21:57.130
Oh, my God.

21:57.154 --> 21:59.465
Porsha, what are you doing here?

21:59.489 --> 22:01.534
Working, scouting talent.

22:01.558 --> 22:03.002
What y'all doing here,

22:03.026 --> 22:04.937
crossing enemy lines and whatnot?

22:04.961 --> 22:09.409
We are here to prove that
a little karaoke and tequila

22:09.433 --> 22:11.611
will bring the Sasha Fierce
out of anybody, right?

22:11.635 --> 22:13.680
Now drink up, everybody.
Clink, clink, clink.

22:13.704 --> 22:15.581
Think you can give us
a little Chaka Khan?

22:15.605 --> 22:18.017
Uh, just a little, just a little bit,

22:18.041 --> 22:19.752
just for the table.

22:19.776 --> 22:21.554
I-I don't... I don't know, maybe.

22:21.578 --> 22:23.089
Come on, we are here
supporting you, okay?

22:23.113 --> 22:24.257
We got you.

22:24.281 --> 22:27.432
Please, Lord, just a little sound.

22:29.720 --> 22:31.030
Okay.

22:35.692 --> 22:39.939
♪ I'm every woman ♪

22:39.963 --> 22:43.342
♪ It's all in me ♪

22:43.366 --> 22:44.544
♪ Anything ♪

22:44.568 --> 22:46.245
♪ You want done, baby ♪

22:46.269 --> 22:47.780
♪ I'll do it natu... ♪

22:47.804 --> 22:49.015
- Hi.
- Oh, hey.

22:49.039 --> 22:50.850
That song is too high
in your register.

22:50.874 --> 22:52.085
Wow, excuse you.

22:52.109 --> 22:54.287
I think that we will
be the judge of that.

22:54.311 --> 22:56.789
Honey, if little Chaka could,
Chaka would,

22:56.813 --> 22:58.291
but clearly, baby, Chaka can't.

22:58.315 --> 22:59.859
Okay.

22:59.883 --> 23:01.227
Besides, she wants
to sing on my stage,

23:01.251 --> 23:02.495
she'll sing what I give her.

23:02.519 --> 23:04.297
Name?

23:04.321 --> 23:05.898
Lala.

23:05.922 --> 23:07.133
All right, Lala, you're up next.

23:07.157 --> 23:09.502
Keep those vocals warm.

23:09.526 --> 23:10.937
If you can find a vocal.

23:10.961 --> 23:12.772
Okay, so, she actually wasn't wrong.

23:12.796 --> 23:15.241
- But you told her.
- Mm, I did, I did!

23:15.265 --> 23:16.442
She got the message.

23:16.466 --> 23:18.344
- Oh, did she really?
- Yeah...

23:18.368 --> 23:20.413
Okay, so this is what we're gonna do.

23:20.437 --> 23:22.815
Get ready to meet your son.

23:28.979 --> 23:30.828
Hey, little man!

23:32.983 --> 23:34.827
He's not breathing.

23:36.853 --> 23:38.264
Get this baby on a respirator!

23:38.288 --> 23:39.966
Can I get vitals on the baby?

23:39.990 --> 23:42.101
What? W-what do you mean
he's not breathing?

23:42.125 --> 23:44.170
- She's hemorrhaging!
- Get her stabilized.

23:44.194 --> 23:45.404
Get him out of here.

23:45.428 --> 23:47.273
I'm sorry, Mr. Lyon,
but you have to leave.

23:47.297 --> 23:49.642
You can't! I'm not leaving my son!

23:49.666 --> 23:51.444
Get the cart.

23:51.468 --> 23:53.513
I'm not leaving my son!

23:53.537 --> 23:54.914
Mr. Lyon, you have to leave.

23:54.938 --> 23:56.516
She's losing a lot of blood!

23:56.540 --> 23:59.118
Help my wife! Help her, please!

23:59.142 --> 24:01.420
- What are her vitals?
- She's hypotensive.

24:01.444 --> 24:02.588
More pads?

24:02.612 --> 24:04.190
She's bleeding out!

24:17.893 --> 24:20.644
Something went wrong, didn't it?

24:23.065 --> 24:26.311
I'm sorry, Quincy. Um...

24:26.335 --> 24:28.247
My mom trusted you
to take care of her,

24:28.271 --> 24:30.220
and so did I!

24:32.742 --> 24:34.720
If she dies...

24:34.744 --> 24:36.555
it's on you!

25:59.261 --> 26:01.773
Oh, my God.

26:14.310 --> 26:15.754
Everything's all set.

26:15.778 --> 26:18.423
He'll have the money in the morning.

26:18.447 --> 26:20.659
The morning?

26:20.683 --> 26:23.295
Yeah, he's probably go to
go to the bank or something.

26:23.319 --> 26:25.969
It's a bit more than
what I usually ask for.

26:28.224 --> 26:30.168
All righty, then.

26:30.192 --> 26:34.373
You're having second thoughts?

26:34.397 --> 26:38.543
It's just, like, I ain't
never met nobody like you.

26:38.567 --> 26:39.811
You got me thinking

26:39.835 --> 26:43.348
I'm this close to being free
from everything.

26:43.372 --> 26:44.950
Yeah.

26:44.974 --> 26:47.185
You're afraid.

26:47.209 --> 26:50.255
You are afraid of who you might be

26:50.279 --> 26:52.162
if you're not Lucious Lyon.

26:54.283 --> 26:56.828
Let me tell you something,
little lady.

26:56.852 --> 26:59.164
I ain't afraid of a damn thing.

26:59.188 --> 27:01.767
I'm the baddest man
in the whole damn land.

27:01.791 --> 27:04.169
The baddest, huh?

27:04.193 --> 27:07.672
Lucious, you have a beautiful family

27:07.696 --> 27:09.674
that you've told me about.

27:09.698 --> 27:13.178
And you built a whole empire.

27:13.202 --> 27:16.014
That's quite a legacy.

27:16.038 --> 27:17.382
It's just weird

27:17.406 --> 27:20.585
thinking about leaving it
all behind, you know?

27:20.609 --> 27:22.988
When I had cancer,

27:23.012 --> 27:25.891
I was sure
I was gonna die in that bed.

27:27.450 --> 27:30.262
But that was not the end of my story,

27:30.286 --> 27:32.030
just like...

27:32.054 --> 27:35.567
this is not the end of yours.

27:35.591 --> 27:37.602
It's not.

27:39.128 --> 27:40.705
You're right.

27:42.765 --> 27:45.243
We could write new chapters...

27:45.267 --> 27:46.678
- Yes?
- Together.

27:53.843 --> 27:55.987
- Center yourself.
- And go.

27:56.011 --> 27:57.556
You got it, you got it, you got it.

27:57.580 --> 28:00.258
Fly little birdy, fly!

28:00.282 --> 28:02.160
This was a good idea, Becky.

28:02.184 --> 28:03.562
I think I'm gonna go up
right after her.

28:03.586 --> 28:04.763
No.

28:04.787 --> 28:07.732
- ♪ I'm every woman ♪
- No, no, no, no.

28:07.756 --> 28:09.501
I'm gonna commandeer that, thank you.

28:09.525 --> 28:11.703
Come here, girl.

28:11.727 --> 28:13.205
Don't be nervous.

28:13.229 --> 28:15.974
You can sing, you're just
not placing your voice right.

28:15.998 --> 28:17.209
- Okay.
- Okay?

28:17.233 --> 28:18.877
I want you to stay
on top of your breath.

28:18.901 --> 28:20.712
Make it come from your diaphragm,

28:20.736 --> 28:21.713
so sing from down here.

28:21.737 --> 28:22.714
- Diaphragm.
- Not up here.

28:22.738 --> 28:24.649
- Not up here.
- Okay?

28:24.673 --> 28:27.152
Pull your shoulders back, okay?

28:27.176 --> 28:29.321
Your song has got to come
from your heart, baby,

28:29.345 --> 28:30.622
not your head.

28:30.646 --> 28:31.623
- Okay.
- Okay?

28:31.647 --> 28:32.891
You got this.

28:49.832 --> 28:52.644
♪ I will love you any way ♪

28:52.668 --> 28:55.580
♪ Even if you cannot stay ♪

28:55.604 --> 28:58.483
♪ I think you are the one for me ♪

28:58.507 --> 29:01.653
♪ Here is where you ought to be ♪

29:01.677 --> 29:04.222
♪ I just want to satisfy ya ♪

29:04.246 --> 29:07.659
♪ Though you're not mine,
I can't deny ya ♪

29:07.683 --> 29:10.462
♪ Don't you hear me talking, baby? ♪

29:10.486 --> 29:13.231
♪ Love me now, or I'll go crazy ♪

29:13.255 --> 29:17.469
♪ Oh, oh, sweet thing ♪

29:17.493 --> 29:22.040
♪ Don't you know
you're my everything? ♪

29:22.064 --> 29:26.177
♪ Oh, oh, sweet thing ♪

29:26.201 --> 29:31.049
♪ Don't you know
you're my everything? ♪

29:31.073 --> 29:32.617
♪ Yes, you are ♪

29:32.641 --> 29:34.185
I can work with this!

29:34.209 --> 29:35.854
Yes.

29:35.878 --> 29:37.522
I told you.

29:37.546 --> 29:41.126
I know talent when I see it.

29:43.652 --> 29:46.131
♪ Give me that love ♪

29:46.155 --> 29:47.465
I like the bridge...

29:47.489 --> 29:48.533
but that's about it.

29:48.557 --> 29:50.502
Yeah, I mean, I think it's hot.

29:50.526 --> 29:51.636
It's just...

29:51.660 --> 29:54.706
the track is way too overproduced.

29:54.730 --> 29:56.975
But what I'm really trying
to figure out is...

29:56.999 --> 29:58.643
what's up with these lyrics?

29:58.667 --> 29:59.945
What you mean?

29:59.969 --> 30:01.780
I mean, you up in here

30:01.804 --> 30:03.848
talking about
wining and dining some girl

30:03.872 --> 30:05.884
to play house with you?

30:07.676 --> 30:08.956
Don't nobody want to play house.

30:10.079 --> 30:11.823
You're a whole comedian today, huh?

30:11.847 --> 30:14.125
No, I'm sorry.

30:14.149 --> 30:16.394
But for real though, like...

30:16.418 --> 30:19.497
Where's the passion?

30:19.521 --> 30:21.266
You know?

30:21.290 --> 30:23.868
Is this really what you want to say?

30:25.594 --> 30:27.505
I don't know anymore, T.

30:27.529 --> 30:30.108
It's like I...

30:30.132 --> 30:32.616
I haven't been inspired...

30:34.470 --> 30:36.715
Since you and me
stopped talking, really.

30:36.739 --> 30:39.351
♪ Make you feel good,
baby, I'm stuck on you ♪

30:39.375 --> 30:42.087
I was just trying to give you space.

30:42.111 --> 30:43.955
Staying celibate
to finish your album...

30:43.979 --> 30:45.390
hey, I respect that.

30:45.414 --> 30:47.392
Baby...

30:47.416 --> 30:49.227
my album's done.

30:49.251 --> 30:52.197
♪ I need it like that morning coffee ♪

30:52.221 --> 30:54.499
♪ This feeling,
it don't come by often ♪

30:54.523 --> 30:57.402
♪ But I got you now,
promise won't let you down ♪

30:57.426 --> 30:59.270
♪ I've been struck by you ♪

30:59.294 --> 31:01.072
Ain't nobody over there.

31:01.096 --> 31:02.607
♪ I'm glad I found you ♪

31:02.631 --> 31:06.911
I know exactly what you need
to find some new inspiration.

31:06.935 --> 31:08.780
And it's what I need, too.

31:08.804 --> 31:10.782
♪ Baby, I'm stuck on you ♪

31:10.806 --> 31:13.718
♪ Make you feel good,
make you feel good ♪

31:13.742 --> 31:17.055
♪ Make you feel good,
baby, I'm stuck on you ♪

31:17.079 --> 31:19.224
♪ Make you feel good,
make you feel good ♪

31:19.248 --> 31:20.959
- ♪ I just wanna ♪
- ♪ Make you feel good ♪

31:20.983 --> 31:23.595
♪ 'Cause, baby, I'm stuck on you ♪

31:23.619 --> 31:25.997
♪ Make you feel good ♪

31:27.523 --> 31:30.435
♪ I want to make you
feel so good, baby ♪

32:04.426 --> 32:06.504
What do You want from me?

32:09.098 --> 32:10.909
What do You want from me?

32:23.345 --> 32:26.357
That what You want, huh?

32:26.381 --> 32:28.193
You want a sacrifice?

32:30.252 --> 32:31.496
I'll give you back your heart

32:31.520 --> 32:33.331
if you save my wife and my child.

32:33.355 --> 32:34.999
Save my family.

32:36.992 --> 32:38.803
I'll give you your heart. Save 'em.

32:38.827 --> 32:39.827
Take me.

32:53.672 --> 32:55.117
- Andre!
- Come on!

32:55.141 --> 32:56.385
- Andre, what the...
- Take me!

32:56.409 --> 32:57.886
Andre, what the hell
are you doing in here?

32:57.910 --> 33:00.355
Andre!

33:00.379 --> 33:01.790
Drop it! Let it go!

33:01.814 --> 33:03.125
It's my fault, Ma.

33:03.149 --> 33:04.493
What? What are you talking about?

33:04.517 --> 33:06.728
- God's making this happen.
